The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, March 23: Philip Yeo, the special adviser to the Singapore Prime Minister, met Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today and said his country was interested in making Bengal an invest- ment destination.     
	Yeo said: We want to make investments in this state I also told him (the chief minister) Nayachar was a nice place and the proposed PCPIR (chemical hub) there would lead to creation of employment opportunities.        
	Calcutta: The Supreme Court has admitted a petition demanding cancellation of the bail of CPM leader Suhrid Dutta and party supporter Debu Malik. The duo, convicted in the Tapasi Malik rape and murder case, were sentenced to life by a trial court but given bail by Calcutta High Court.                                                                                                                                                                       
